@page "/docs/tableofcontents"
@using Mudx.Docs.Outline

<PageTitle>Table Of Contents</PageTitle>

<DocsPage>
    <DocsPageHeader Title="Outline">
        <Description>
            A scrollspy control for displaying an index or table of contents on either side of the text content.
            Typically you would surround the document with <CodeInline>MudXOutline</CodeInline> and each individual
            section with <CodeInline>MudXOutlineSection</CodeInline>.
        </Description>
    </DocsPageHeader>

    <DocsPageSection Title="Basic Usage">
        <Description>
            The outline is a scrollspy control for displaying an index or table of contents on either side of the text content.
            The <CodeInline>MudXOutline</CodeInline> is a wrapper for a number of <CodeInline>MudXOutlineSection</CodeInline>. 
            Each <CodeInline>MudXOutlineSection</CodeInline> has a <CodeInline>Title</CodeInline> that is used for the index 
            and whatever content is supplied inside is what is displayed in the main content area. By default the control
            requires very minimal setup, however to nest it inside another be sure to set the <CodeInline>ScrollContainerSelector</CodeInline>
            to the outer element with a scrollbar as scrollspy will only work if a scrollbar is present. Remember when using the Selector to
            preface a class with a . or an id with a #.
        </Description>
        <SectionContent>
            <OutlineBasicExample />
        </SectionContent>
    </DocsPageSection>

    <DocsPageSection Title="Index Customization">
        <Description>
            There are many properties you can change to customize the look and feel of the control, but ultimately
            the content is strictly upon you to style and use. <CodeInline>Anchor</CodeInline> and 
            <CodeInline>Width</CodeInline> are most common.
        </Description>
        <SectionContent>
            <OutlineCustomizeExample />
        </SectionContent>
    </DocsPageSection>

    <DocsPageSection Title="Scroll Style">
        <Description>
            You can customize the Variant used for the ScrollSpy by setting the <CodeInline>StyleVariant</CodeInline>
            property. Available options are <CodeInline>None</CodeInline>, <CodeInline>Bullet</CodeInline>, 
            <CodeInline>Scroll</CodeInline> and <CodeInline>Minimal</CodeInline>.
        </Description>
        <SectionContent>
            <OutlineVariantExample />
        </SectionContent>
    </DocsPageSection>

</DocsPage>

